    <note type="biography">
        <p>Scottish physician and botanist. Entered the Bengal medical service in 1854. Superintendent, Calcutta botanic garden, 1861–8; conservator of forests, Bengal, 1864–6; retired because of ill health. Instituted experiments that led to the successful cultivation of <hi rend="italic">Cinchona</hi> in India.</p></note>
